# Security Architecture
## 8-Layer Defense Stack

```mermaid
graph TD
    REQ[Incoming Request] --> L1

    subgraph LAYER1[" Layer 1: Authentication "]
        L1{ auth.mode? }
        L1 -->|none| PERMIT[✅ Allow (localhost only)]
        L1 -->|token| TOKEN{Validate<br/>Bearer token}
        L1 -->|password| PASS{Verify<br/>bcrypt hash}
        L1 -->|trusted-proxy| PROXY{Check<br/>X-Forwarded-For}
        L1 -->|invalid| DENY1[❌ 401 Unauthorized]
        TOKEN -->|valid| PERMIT
        TOKEN -->|invalid| DENY1
        PASS -->|valid| PERMIT
        PASS -->|invalid| DENY1
        PROXY -->|trusted| PERMIT
        PROXY -->|untrusted| DENY1
    end

    PERMIT --> L2
    subgraph LAYER2[" Layer 2: Role & Scopes "]
        L2{role?}
        L2 -->|operator| OP[Full access<br/>+ approvals]
        L2 -->|user| USER[Chat + limited tools]
        L2 -->|internal| SYS[System services]
    end

    OP & USER & SYS --> L3
    subgraph LAYER3[" Layer 3: Tool Policy "]
        L3{policy?}
        L3 -->|messaging| MSG[Only send/read msg]
        L3 -->|minimal| MIN[Read/write files<br/>approved bash]
        L3 -->|full| FULL[All tools<br/>(includes dangerous)]
    end

    MSG & MIN & FULL --> L4
    subgraph LAYER4[" Layer 4: Approval System "]
        L4{Requires approval?}
        L4 -->|Yes| APPROVAL{Pending<br/>operator OK?}
        L4 -->|No| SKIP[Skip approval]
        APPROVAL -->|Approved| EXEC[Execute]
        APPROVAL -->|Denied/Timeout| BLOCK[❌ Block]
        APPROVAL -->|No response| TIMEOUT[❌ Timeout]
    end

    SKIP --> L5
    EXEC --> L5
    BLOCK --> LOG[Security Log<br/>📝Audit trail]
    TIMEOUT --> LOG

    subgraph LAYER5[" Layer 5: Prompt Injection Defense "]
        L5[Wrap user content<br/>in XML tags<br/>Strip control chars<br/>Apply 13 regex patterns]
    end

    L5 --> L6
    subgraph LAYER6[" Layer 6: Sandbox Execution "]
        L6{sandbox.level?}
        L6 -->|none| RUN[Run unrestricted<br/>⚠️  risky]
        L6 -->|workspace| WS[Restrict to<br/>agent workspace]
        L6 -->|strict| STRICT[Allowlist bins<br/>+ paths]
        L6 -->|container| DOCKER[Docker<br/>isolation]
    end

    RUN & WS & STRICT & DOCKER --> L7
    subgraph LAYER7[" Layer 7: Secrets Management "]
        L7[No plaintext keys<br/>Use $ref pattern<br/>Keychain / cred manager<br/>Rotate on compromise]
    end

    L7 --> L8
    subgraph LAYER8[" Layer 8: Security Audit "]
        L8[detect-secrets scan<br/>dangerous-config check<br/>file permission audit<br/>network egress monitor]
    end

    L8 --> FINAL[🤖 Agent<br/>(Still untrusted!)]
    LOG --> FINAL

    %% Styling
    style L4 fill:#ffebee,stroke:#f44336,stroke-width:3px
    style L6 fill:#fff3e0,stroke:#ff9800,stroke-width:2px
    style L8 fill:#e8eaf6,stroke:#3f51b5,stroke-width:2px
    style DENY1 fill:#ffcdd2,stroke:#c62828
    style BLOCK fill:#ffcdd2,stroke:#c62828
    style TIMEOUT fill:#ffecb3,stroke:#ff8f00
    style FINAL fill:#f5f5f5,stroke:#616161
```

**Layer 1: Authentication (4 modes)**

| Mode | Use Case | Example |
|------|----------|---------|
| `none` | Localhost only, trusted network | Development, single-user |
| `token` | API access, cloud deployment | `Authorization: Bearer xyz` |
| `password` | Manual UI access | Basic auth prompt |
| `trusted-proxy` | Behind Nginx/Cloudflare | `X-Forwarded-For` from trusted IPs |

**Layer 4: Approval System**

Tools requiring approval (configurable):
- `run_bash` with dangerous commands (`rm`, `sudo`, `dd`, `mkfs`)
- `delete_file` outside workspace
- `git_push` to protected branches
- `send_email` to external recipients
- `browser_*` with sensitive sites (banking, corporate)

**Approval flow:**
```
User → Agent → Tool needs approval → Notification to operator →
Operator UI: [Approve] [Deny] [Always allow] → Execute/Block
```

**Layer 5: Injection Defense**

13 regex patterns detect:
- Unicode homoglyphs (fаke Cyrillic а)
- XML/HTML tag injection
- Command injection (`;`, `&&`, `|`)
- Path traversal (`../`, `..\\`)
- Prompt escape sequences (`\x1b`, `\u202e`)

**Layer 6: Sandbox Levels**

| Level | Isolation | Use Case |
|-------|-----------|----------|
| `none` | None | Trusted internal agents |
| `workspace` | Filesystem仅限于 workspace | Default for user agents |
| `strict` | Allowlist bins + paths | Production, multi-user |
| `container` | Docker container (planned) | High-security environments |

